	       <p align="justify" style="font-size:20px; font-family:Helvetica">
		 Oinam Meitei is a postdoctoral associate at the Massachusetts Institute of Technology in the group of Troy Van Voorhis. He received his B.Sc. in Chemistry from Madras Christian College, Chennai, in 2013 and his M.Sc. in Chemistry from Visvesvaraya National Institute of Technology, Nagpur, in 2015. During the summers of 2013 and 2014, he was a Summer Research Fellow at National Chemical Laboratory, Pune. He then moved to Germany and earned his Ph.D. in theoretical chemistry from Friedrich-Alexander University, Erlangen, in 2018, advised by Andreas Hesselmann. He moved to the US again, and from 2019 to 2021, he was a postdoctoral researcher at Virginia Tech, Blackburg, with Nicholas Mayhall.
	       </p>
